The President has signed an Executive Order terminating the national emergency declared with respect to Côte d'Ivoire, acknowledging the country's progress since the end of its civil war in 2011. This includes successful presidential elections in October 2015 and improvements in managing the flow of arms and combating illicit trafficking of natural resources. The United States congratulates the people of Côte d'Ivoire for their resilience and commitment to peace, democracy, and prosperity. Economic sanctions imposed on Côte d'Ivoire have also been lifted. While challenges remain, such as land reform and ensuring equitable economic growth, the United States remains committed to supporting Côte d'Ivoire in its efforts towards national reconciliation and security sector reform. The United States looks forward to celebrating more achievements as Côte d'Ivoire continues to rebuild and regain its position as an economic engine and vibrant democracy in West Africa.